00:03:00.670 --> 00:03:02.540
Once the users are
on the Play Store,

00:03:02.540 --> 00:03:05.764
how do they discover your app?

00:03:05.764 --> 00:03:08.180
So that's why we need to talk
about search on Google Play.

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:09.810
I'll start with search.

00:03:09.810 --> 00:03:12.891
For the average app,
search makes a large share

00:03:12.891 --> 00:03:13.390
of installs.

00:03:13.390 --> 00:03:14.760
I think we all know that.

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:17.062
As an app developer,
when a user searches

00:03:17.062 --> 00:03:19.520
for something that's like your
app, what do you want to do?

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:21.500
You want them to find
your app first, right?

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:23.530
And optimizing
that process means

00:03:23.530 --> 00:03:26.550
understanding the types of
searches that users are doing

00:03:26.550 --> 00:03:29.270
and making sure that
the data for your app

00:03:29.270 --> 00:03:34.270
supports these searches so that
we can surface these to users.

00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:37.007
So what are the types of
searches that users do on Play?

00:03:37.007 --> 00:03:38.340
There are two types of searches.

00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:40.584
The first is searching by title.

00:03:40.584 --> 00:03:42.500
This is when a user knows
exactly what they're

00:03:42.500 --> 00:03:42.950
looking for.

00:03:42.950 --> 00:03:44.150
They know the title of your app.

00:03:44.150 --> 00:03:46.150
So all they do is just type
in the title of your app

00:03:46.150 --> 00:03:46.983
into the search bar.

00:03:46.983 --> 00:03:50.614
And they do that
search based on that.

00:03:50.614 --> 00:03:51.530
What's important here?

00:03:51.530 --> 00:03:53.321
The really important
thing to remember here

00:03:53.321 --> 00:03:56.300
is that a high-quality
title is really, really key.

00:03:56.300 --> 00:03:58.120
Titles are not just
about branding.

00:03:58.120 --> 00:04:01.200
It's important to be as clear
as possible in the title

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:03.830
to communicate what
the app is about

00:04:03.830 --> 00:04:07.060
and what it does
for the user, right?

00:04:07.060 --> 00:04:08.910
Is your app about
internet radio?

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:10.460
Is your app about
travel planning?

00:04:10.460 --> 00:04:11.900
Is it about podcasting?

00:04:11.900 --> 00:04:13.580
Make this clear in
the title so that you

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:15.980
capture the attention
of interested users.

00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:18.940
That also makes your app stand
out in a sea of competitors.

00:04:18.940 --> 00:04:21.539
And it also helps us surface
you in relevant search queries.

00:04:24.380 --> 00:04:26.300
Second type of
search that users do

00:04:26.300 --> 00:04:29.794
is when they don't know exactly
what they're looking for,

00:04:29.794 --> 00:04:31.210
and they're searching
by keywords.

00:04:31.210 --> 00:04:32.710
And these keywords
might correspond

00:04:32.710 --> 00:04:34.610
to features in your
app or characteristics

00:04:34.610 --> 00:04:35.750
of your app or game.

00:04:35.750 --> 00:04:37.660
So for example, my friend
might tell me, hey,

00:04:37.660 --> 00:04:39.540
there's this new cool game out.

00:04:39.540 --> 00:04:42.240
It has something to do with
puzzles and goblins, right?

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:44.300
So I might search for
puzzle games with goblins

00:04:44.300 --> 00:04:46.977
and see what comes out of there.

00:04:46.977 --> 00:04:48.560
What supports these
kinds of searches?

00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:51.370
This is where your store
listing is really important.

00:04:51.370 --> 00:04:56.570
Your app's description should
clearly tell us and tell users

00:04:56.570 --> 00:04:59.760
what your app does and why
it matches to users, right?

00:04:59.760 --> 00:05:02.430
Make sure that you get all
that information up front.

00:05:02.430 --> 00:05:04.000
And once that's
done, then you can

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:05.795
brag about how
successful your app is,

00:05:05.795 --> 00:05:07.420
all the awards you've
won and so forth.

00:05:07.420 --> 00:05:09.040
But make sure front and
center right at the top

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:10.755
tells what your app
does, why it matters.

00:05:14.480 --> 00:05:16.420
So getting users to
your store listing

00:05:16.420 --> 00:05:20.490
to land on there from search is
just one part of the equation.

00:05:20.490 --> 00:05:23.120
The other part is getting them
to download, hit that Install

00:05:23.120 --> 00:05:24.750
button, convert
them in that way,

00:05:24.750 --> 00:05:26.400
reaching the users that way.

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:29.030
So keep in mind that there
are many users out there who

00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:31.795
judge apps by the quality of
the screenshots and videos.

00:05:31.795 --> 00:05:33.670
Because if you haven't
downloaded an app yet,

00:05:33.670 --> 00:05:34.920
there's no other
way you can tell

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:37.530
what that app is like when you
actually have it on your phone.

00:05:37.530 --> 00:05:39.480
So make sure you have
high-quality screenshots

00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:42.150
and videos that the
user can scan through.

00:05:42.150 --> 00:05:45.440
And the more you can communicate
what the app experience is

00:05:45.440 --> 00:05:49.010
like, the more likely it is that
users will download your app.

00:05:51.777 --> 00:05:53.610
Of course, you don't
have to do all the work

00:05:53.610 --> 00:05:54.750
when it comes to search.

00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:57.450
Google Play is constantly
collecting statistics

00:05:57.450 --> 00:05:59.490
about installs,
uninstalls, and install

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:01.020
retention and engagement.

00:06:01.020 --> 00:06:03.470
And apps that are successful
in all of these metrics

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:06.520
are more likely to be highly
ranked in search results.

00:06:06.520 --> 00:06:07.560
So what does that mean?

00:06:07.560 --> 00:06:09.840
It means that the most
important thing you can do

00:06:09.840 --> 00:06:12.680
is to create the best
experience for your users

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:14.030
no matter what your app does.

00:06:14.030 --> 00:06:15.900
Because if you've got a
great app that users love,

00:06:15.900 --> 00:06:17.066
they're going to install it.

00:06:17.066 --> 00:06:18.570
They're less likely
to uninstall it.

00:06:18.570 --> 00:06:20.140
If they do uninstall
it at some point,

00:06:20.140 --> 00:06:21.940
they will keep it for a
long time, finish playing

00:06:21.940 --> 00:06:24.030
through the game, whatever,
before they uninstall it.

00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:24.785
And they will be very engaged.

00:06:24.785 --> 00:06:26.607
They'll spend a lot
of time on your app.

00:06:26.607 --> 00:06:28.440
And these are the signals
that we pick up on

00:06:28.440 --> 00:06:30.200
to recognize what is
a high-quality app.

00:06:33.410 --> 00:06:35.570
So sometimes users
might just want

00:06:35.570 --> 00:06:38.370
to browse through the Play Store
and check on new apps, right?

00:06:38.370 --> 00:06:39.580
That's discovery by browsing.

00:06:39.580 --> 00:06:41.163
And there are generally
two categories

00:06:41.163 --> 00:06:42.310
that browsing falls into.

00:06:42.310 --> 00:06:44.950
The first is browsing
on the Apps homepage,

00:06:44.950 --> 00:06:48.950
and the second is browsing
through top charts.

00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:50.450
So when a user opens
the Play Store,

00:06:50.450 --> 00:06:51.610
we all know where
the Apps homepage is.

00:06:51.610 --> 00:06:54.110
You tap Apps, and then you get
to this place called the Apps

00:06:54.110 --> 00:06:54.630
homepage.

00:06:54.630 --> 00:06:57.440
And here is where
users can discover apps

00:06:57.440 --> 00:06:59.390
from different clusters
and categories.

00:06:59.390 --> 00:07:01.700
For example, they might
find new and updated apps,

00:07:01.700 --> 00:07:03.960
health and fitness apps,
communication apps.

00:07:03.960 --> 00:07:05.880
And this page is
personalized for each user,

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.070
so remember that.

00:07:07.070 --> 00:07:09.780
So the Apps homepage is
a browsing experience

00:07:09.780 --> 00:07:12.150
that let's Google
Play offer great apps

00:07:12.150 --> 00:07:15.950
that the user may
be interested in.

00:07:15.950 --> 00:07:17.330
And finally there's top charts.

00:07:17.330 --> 00:07:19.870
So these lists, like
top-selling, top apps,

00:07:19.870 --> 00:07:23.440
top grossing, top new,
trending, are common ways

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:25.360
that we provide for
both new and returning

00:07:25.360 --> 00:07:28.200
users to quickly discover
the most popular apps.

00:07:31.040 --> 00:07:33.820
So that's search and discovery
on Play, some quick little tips

00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:35.846
on how to improve
discoverability.

00:07:35.846 --> 00:07:38.220
Now I'd like to talk about a
few more concrete things you

00:07:38.220 --> 00:07:41.250
