your app outside of Play.

00:07:44.240 --> 00:07:45.460
So you've built your app.

00:07:45.460 --> 00:07:47.060
You've published it.

00:07:47.060 --> 00:07:48.480
You obviously want
to publicize it

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:51.264
on your website, marketing
material, ad campaigns,

00:07:51.264 --> 00:07:52.680
social media
channels, everything.

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:53.970
Get it out there.

00:07:53.970 --> 00:07:55.912
Remember to use Google
Play official badging

00:07:55.912 --> 00:07:56.620
when you do that.

00:07:56.620 --> 00:07:57.430
That's really important.

00:07:57.430 --> 00:07:57.960
Why?

00:07:57.960 --> 00:08:02.030
Because users are 47% more
likely to trust and download

00:08:02.030 --> 00:08:03.575
your app when they
see that badge.

00:08:07.190 --> 00:08:09.550
If you happen to have a web
service that accompanies

00:08:09.550 --> 00:08:13.902
your mobile app or users
use your service across web

00:08:13.902 --> 00:08:15.360
and mobile, it
makes a lot of sense

00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:18.280
to also consider using Google
sign-in on your website

00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:20.880
so that users who sign
in with a Google account

00:08:20.880 --> 00:08:23.800
have the option to
send your app directly

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:25.021
to their device over the air.

00:08:25.021 --> 00:08:26.520
It just works like
that, like magic.

00:08:26.520 --> 00:08:28.710
You sign in one time
on your website.

00:08:28.710 --> 00:08:31.760
The user gets this button
that says Install On Device.

00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:34.774
You tap that, bang, it appears
on your device seconds later.

00:08:34.774 --> 00:08:37.190
And what's even better is that
once the user is signing in

00:08:37.190 --> 00:08:39.760
on your device, he's
also automatically signed

00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:40.804
in on the app.

00:08:40.804 --> 00:08:42.470
So there's no friction
at all in getting

00:08:42.470 --> 00:08:45.330
that user into
your app that way.

00:08:45.330 --> 00:08:49.170
So developers have seen
a 40% install acceptance

00:08:49.170 --> 00:08:49.965
rate using this.

00:08:49.965 --> 00:08:52.256
So this is really worth doing,
really worth trying out.

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:57.680
Now we all know
that social media

00:08:57.680 --> 00:09:00.140
is really important
for acquiring users.

00:09:00.140 --> 00:09:02.260
And YouTube is a great
marketing channel

00:09:02.260 --> 00:09:05.300
for apps, especially games.

00:09:05.300 --> 00:09:09.070
We have a huge audience of
potentially interested users.

00:09:09.070 --> 00:09:13.980
And this survey by Blitz
found that about 95% of gamers

00:09:13.980 --> 00:09:17.430
discover new games by watching
gameplay videos or trailers.

00:09:17.430 --> 00:09:20.670
That's significantly more
than the percentage of users

00:09:20.670 --> 00:09:23.950
who discover games by reading
reviews, going to game makers'

00:09:23.950 --> 00:09:25.420
websites, and so forth.

00:09:25.420 --> 00:09:27.620
So think about creating
a YouTube channel

00:09:27.620 --> 00:09:31.100
to share your game trailers,
to share gameplay videos, game

00:09:31.100 --> 00:09:33.390
tips, even user-generated
content around your games

00:09:33.390 --> 00:09:35.540
if you're a game developer,
to engage and acquire

00:09:35.540 --> 00:09:37.195
potential new users.

00:09:37.195 --> 00:09:38.910
If you're an app
developer, think

00:09:38.910 --> 00:09:40.710
about how this might
apply to you as well.

00:09:40.710 --> 00:09:43.909
Maybe you want to create-- if
it's, for example, a utility

00:09:43.909 --> 00:09:45.950
or productivity app, you
want to create a channel

00:09:45.950 --> 00:09:48.620
that shares tips around
how you can use your app

00:09:48.620 --> 00:09:51.090
to drive productivity
in your life.

00:09:54.300 --> 00:09:58.080
Finally, one more thing you
can do to acquire more users,

00:09:58.080 --> 00:10:01.645
