00:11:25.019 --> 00:11:27.560
Take some time to think about
how you could possibly leverage

00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:30.430
some of these to actually
make your app stand out,

00:11:30.430 --> 00:11:31.500
stand out from the crowd.

00:11:34.660 --> 00:11:37.480
When I speak to app
developers, the first thing

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:39.580
that jumps to mind when
it comes to app promotion

00:11:39.580 --> 00:11:41.820
is in-app promotion.

00:11:41.820 --> 00:11:43.870
However, when you
think about your user,

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:46.340
your user can be found in
multiple different places.

00:11:46.340 --> 00:11:49.530
And it's not just
about an app promotion.

00:11:49.530 --> 00:11:51.430
Every day, our
advertising solutions

00:11:51.430 --> 00:11:54.240
are becoming smarter
and more effective.

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:56.460
We currently have the
ability to advertise

00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:58.960
on three great platforms.

00:11:58.960 --> 00:12:01.290
There are 2 billion
video hours watched

00:12:01.290 --> 00:12:04.170
on YouTube mobile per month.

00:12:04.170 --> 00:12:07.880
There are 100 billion searches
on google.com per month.

00:12:07.880 --> 00:12:11.980
And through AdMob, we can reach
900 million unique devices

00:12:11.980 --> 00:12:14.210
per month.

00:12:14.210 --> 00:12:15.720
So the question
really comes then,

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:18.280
how do you choose
the right campaign?

00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:19.970
And that logic comes
down to the users

00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:22.212
that you're trying
to engage with.

00:12:22.212 --> 00:12:26.250
Do you just want those
users to download your app

00:12:26.250 --> 00:12:28.937
and actually open it
for once, one time?

00:12:28.937 --> 00:12:30.770
Or do you actually want
them to open that up

00:12:30.770 --> 00:12:32.867
and take a very specific
action and continue

00:12:32.867 --> 00:12:34.825
to open that up and take
very specific actions?

00:12:37.580 --> 00:12:39.709
I was speaking to a
developer the other day.

00:12:39.709 --> 00:12:41.250
She had done a lot
of market research

00:12:41.250 --> 00:12:43.430
about her financial
management app.

00:12:43.430 --> 00:12:47.630
And she found an app that could
really meet a consumer need.

00:12:47.630 --> 00:12:49.950
She developed the app,
and it was brilliant.

00:12:49.950 --> 00:12:53.630
The difficulty she was finding
was actually driving discovery

00:12:53.630 --> 00:12:56.230
and getting that app installed
and for users to actually use

00:12:56.230 --> 00:12:58.120
that app.

00:12:58.120 --> 00:12:59.880
It's a common
conversation that I have,

00:12:59.880 --> 00:13:02.130
and it's one of the
biggest problems.

00:13:02.130 --> 00:13:04.920
You're out there developing
these revolutionary apps

00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:07.640
that consumers and users might
not have even thought about.

00:13:07.640 --> 00:13:12.000
The possibilities within
these apps are untold.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.380
And that's why using things like
YouTube and TrueView campaigns

00:13:15.380 --> 00:13:18.220
is such a great way to
explain what your app does

00:13:18.220 --> 00:13:22.830
to the users that could
potentially be using it.

00:13:22.830 --> 00:13:26.240
These campaigns help reach
people on YouTube who

00:13:26.240 --> 00:13:28.210
are actively watching
or have watched

00:13:28.210 --> 00:13:31.490
videos that are related to
applications like yours,

00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:35.060
or have an interest
in similar apps.

00:13:35.060 --> 00:13:37.560
Ad rules will only
show these ads

00:13:37.560 --> 00:13:41.655
to people on relevant devices,
and not on desktop or computer.

00:13:45.240 --> 00:13:47.740
One of the things that
YouTube is very well known for

00:13:47.740 --> 00:13:49.850
is boosting awareness.

00:13:49.850 --> 00:13:53.290
This is a great example of
when a situation has happened

00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:56.865
and awareness has been boosted.

00:13:56.865 --> 00:14:00.360
Game Of War-- Fire Age was
developed by Machine Zone.

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:03.810
It was the top-grossing
app on iOS and Android.

00:14:03.810 --> 00:14:06.280
The goal for them when they
started their YouTube campaigns

00:14:06.280 --> 00:14:10.070
was to drive a high
volume of engaged users

00:14:10.070 --> 00:14:13.027
to install their app
and play it again.

00:14:13.027 --> 00:14:15.110
Once they launched those
campaigns and the results

00:14:15.110 --> 00:14:19.580
were in, they figured out that
the value of the users coming

00:14:19.580 --> 00:14:23.400
from YouTube and those
campaigns were 15% more valuable

00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:26.280
than any other video platform.

00:14:26.280 --> 00:14:28.830
YouTube is an incredibly
powerful platform to use.

00:14:28.830 --> 00:14:32.970
It can be used for both
branding and performance.

00:14:32.970 --> 00:14:36.272
Performance and Google
search-- the two words

00:14:36.272 --> 00:14:37.105
are very synonymous.

00:14:39.740 --> 00:14:42.580
An increasingly more powerful
way to drive user engagement

00:14:42.580 --> 00:14:45.320
is through the mobile
search network.

00:14:45.320 --> 00:14:48.550
Mobile app install campaigns
on the search network

00:14:48.550 --> 00:14:51.880
help people who are already
looking for apps or businesses

00:14:51.880 --> 00:14:55.140
like yours find your app.

00:14:55.140 --> 00:14:56.990
The key to creating
any successful search

00:14:56.990 --> 00:15:00.440
campaign, as many of you know,
comes down to the keywords.

00:15:00.440 --> 00:15:02.970
And Shannon touched
on it a bit earlier.

00:15:02.970 --> 00:15:06.250
These keywords, and through
the new user interface,

00:15:06.250 --> 00:15:10.290
can be generated through
pulling in keywords

00:15:10.290 --> 00:15:12.270
from Google Play
and Google Search

00:15:12.270 --> 00:15:15.294
to give you a few suggestions
that you could use.

00:15:15.294 --> 00:15:16.710
In addition to
that, you can think

00:15:16.710 --> 00:15:18.084
about what your
app actually does

00:15:18.084 --> 00:15:20.550
and the functionality that
your app has within it

00:15:20.550 --> 00:15:22.370
and use those words
in combination

00:15:22.370 --> 00:15:25.880
with the word "app"-- for
example, hotel app, car app,

00:15:25.880 --> 00:15:27.855
shopping app.

00:15:27.855 --> 00:15:29.230
In addition to
that, you can look

00:15:29.230 --> 00:15:32.096
at brand words, brand keywords
and long-tail keywords.

00:15:32.096 --> 00:15:33.720
These are particularly
useful if you're

00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:37.500
trying to drive towards a
very aggressive target CPI.

00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:46.110
In addition to mobile app
install campaigns on the search

00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:48.620
network, you also
have the ability

00:15:48.620 --> 00:15:52.970
to use mobile app install ad
campaigns with extensions.

00:15:52.970 --> 00:15:56.370
So it's not always
the case that you only

00:15:56.370 --> 00:15:58.600
want to drive app downloads.

00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:01.130
It could be possible that your
web presence is incredibly

00:16:01.130 --> 00:16:03.990
strong, and you have
an equal preference

00:16:03.990 --> 00:16:07.780
to whether you get a website
click or an app download.

00:16:07.780 --> 00:16:10.550
So in this particular
case, using app extensions

00:16:10.550 --> 00:16:12.630
like the ones described
by Rhonda Hanson

00:16:12.630 --> 00:16:16.330
can be an excellent way to
give the user the opportunity

00:16:16.330 --> 00:16:17.670
to do one or the other.

00:16:22.060 --> 00:16:26.640
So as I mentioned before, one
of the most used advertising

00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:30.600
platforms is through
an app or AdMob.

00:16:30.600 --> 00:16:32.305
And these types
of campaigns drive

00:16:32.305 --> 00:16:35.164
a huge volume of impressions.

00:16:35.164 --> 00:16:37.080
Now, that volume of
impressions is a great way

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:39.470
to get your awareness
out there and to make

00:16:39.470 --> 00:16:42.930
users aware of the type
of app that you have.

00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:44.820
They're very easy to set up.

00:16:44.820 --> 00:16:47.140
You literally select
your app and what

00:16:47.140 --> 00:16:49.140
you want to promote
it on, and we'll

00:16:49.140 --> 00:16:52.740
set up the rest of
the campaign for you.

00:16:52.740 --> 00:16:55.590
In the long run, you can
use a conversion optimizer

00:16:55.590 --> 00:16:59.230
as well to maintain that
campaign, that sustainability,

00:16:59.230 --> 00:17:02.060
towards the target CPI.

00:17:02.060 --> 00:17:04.379
The shift of the
focus in the past

00:17:04.379 --> 00:17:06.589
has largely been on these
large burst campaigns that

00:17:06.589 --> 00:17:08.069
would get you up the rankings.

00:17:08.069 --> 00:17:09.907
However, what we see
more and more now

00:17:09.907 --> 00:17:11.990
is marketers and developers
working on longer term

00:17:11.990 --> 00:17:14.329
strategies to make sure
that they can profitably

00:17:14.329 --> 00:17:16.730
drive these app downloads
and then follow that up

00:17:16.730 --> 00:17:17.855
with engagement strategies.

00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:23.410
As we've discovered,
in-app advertising

00:17:23.410 --> 00:17:27.171
is one of the fundamental parts
to an advertising campaign.

00:17:27.171 --> 00:17:32.430
App promotions ads are templated
to create text, banner,

00:17:32.430 --> 00:17:35.700
and interstitial ad
formats, driving users

00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:39.450
to either the iTunes store
or the Google Play Store.

00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:43.170
These ads run on mobile
search, on GDN, and in apps,

00:17:43.170 --> 00:17:45.070
and are the most
effective format

00:17:45.070 --> 00:17:48.060
for driving app downloads.

00:17:48.060 --> 00:17:49.890
Once again, reaching
the right user

00:17:49.890 --> 00:17:52.674
is not just about
in-app promotion.

00:17:52.674 --> 00:17:55.090
Developers and marketers are
looking at more holistic ways

00:17:55.090 --> 00:17:56.720
to reach these consumers.

00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:59.370
And that's done through Google
Search, the Display Network,

00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:00.720
and YouTube.

00:18:00.720 --> 00:18:02.480
And these can all
be done and managed

00:18:02.480 --> 00:18:05.190
through the AdWords interface.

00:18:05.190 --> 00:18:06.480
Remember, these ads are smart.

00:18:06.480 --> 00:18:11.339
They're purpose built to
help drive app downloads.

00:18:11.339 --> 00:18:12.880
The first step, as
I've just covered,

00:18:12.880 --> 00:18:16.460
is very much about discovery,
driving app downloads.

00:18:16.460 --> 00:18:18.950
The second step is
about engagement.

00:18:18.950 --> 00:18:21.200
And this is really where you
get to push that lifetime

00:18:21.200 --> 00:18:22.960
value of your users
and to increase

00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:26.630
the profitability of
your app over time.

00:18:26.630 --> 00:18:30.800
Users need to be kept updated
to what's going on in your app.

00:18:30.800 --> 00:18:32.292
Otherwise it acts as a silo.

00:18:32.292 --> 00:18:33.750
And they never
really know when you

00:18:33.750 --> 00:18:37.440
have new updates or potentially
different games or levels

00:18:37.440 --> 00:18:39.320
that they can play.

00:18:39.320 --> 00:18:41.720
So through paid
promotion, I'll show you

00:18:41.720 --> 00:18:43.610
a couple of ways in
which you can reengage

00:18:43.610 --> 00:18:46.660
with those users over time
to sustainably increase

00:18:46.660 --> 00:18:48.170
the profitability of your app.

00:18:51.810 --> 00:18:55.760
So in order to do that,
there are really two ways.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:58.070
The first is through
app engagement campaigns

00:18:58.070 --> 00:19:00.230
on the Display Network.

00:19:00.230 --> 00:19:03.030
These are app
engagement ads that

00:19:03.030 --> 00:19:05.220
are targeted towards
users who already

00:19:05.220 --> 00:19:07.610
have your app installed.

00:19:07.610 --> 00:19:10.600
It encourages the user
to open up your app

00:19:10.600 --> 00:19:14.010
and to engage again
with the content.

00:19:14.010 --> 00:19:17.270
On the Search Network, it
is a similar principle.

00:19:17.270 --> 00:19:19.620
App engagement campaigns on
the Search Network target

00:19:19.620 --> 00:19:22.870
users who already have
your app installed.

00:19:22.870 --> 00:19:25.830
They drive people
back into the app.

00:19:25.830 --> 00:19:29.590
And the aim is to make the
action relate to the search

00:19:29.590 --> 00:19:34.030
query that they have just
searched on to get them there.

00:19:34.030 --> 00:19:37.310
So the question is, how do you
relate that search query back

00:19:37.310 --> 00:19:39.160
to the content within your app?

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:43.300
And that really comes
down to deep linking.

00:19:43.300 --> 00:19:46.660
For ads on the web, just
to give you an analogy,

00:19:46.660 --> 00:19:49.805
you would have your
landing page example.com.

00:19:49.805 --> 00:19:52.380
But driving users to
example.com might not

00:19:52.380 --> 00:19:53.930
be the best user experience.

00:19:53.930 --> 00:19:55.640
So we make it more specific.

00:19:55.640 --> 00:19:57.840
If this user searches
for shoes, you drive them

00:19:57.840 --> 00:20:00.180
to example.com/shoes.

00:20:00.180 --> 00:20:01.901
That principle is
the same for apps.

00:20:01.901 --> 00:20:03.150
It's just called deep linking.

00:20:06.290 --> 00:20:10.280
So to give you a few examples of
how it could potentially work--

00:20:10.280 --> 00:20:12.060
and some of these might
relate to the apps

00:20:12.060 --> 00:20:14.820
that you actually have--
when a user is logged in

00:20:14.820 --> 00:20:17.690
and they actually have
the app on their device,

00:20:17.690 --> 00:20:20.110
they could search for
flights to Beijing

00:20:20.110 --> 00:20:21.800
on the Google Search Network.

00:20:21.800 --> 00:20:28.541
And you could direct them into
your app to flights to China.

00:20:28.541 --> 00:20:31.040
Winter coats would be another
example where the search would

00:20:31.040 --> 00:20:32.790
be winter coats, and
you could direct them

00:20:32.790 --> 00:20:34.530
into your app on the Coats page.

00:20:34.530 --> 00:20:37.196
And lastly, if the user was
searching for Boston movie

00:20:37.196 --> 00:20:38.945
times, you could direct
them into your app

00:20:38.945 --> 00:20:42.840
to the Boston Showtimes page.

00:20:42.840 --> 00:20:45.460
To give you some gaming
examples as well--

00:20:45.460 --> 00:20:48.080
because they are
kind of interesting.

00:20:48.080 --> 00:20:50.230
If, for example, a
user was searching

00:20:50.230 --> 00:20:52.980
on the Search Network
for a gaming app,

00:20:52.980 --> 00:20:54.680
you could potentially
show them an ad

00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:57.141
that's related to that
query if they once again had

00:20:57.141 --> 00:20:58.890
your app installed on
their phone already,

00:20:58.890 --> 00:21:01.400
or their tablet, driving
them back into your app

00:21:01.400 --> 00:21:03.500
to a page that said Play Again.

00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:05.960
And once again, instead of
them looking for other apps

00:21:05.960 --> 00:21:07.751
to download, other
gaming apps to download,

00:21:07.751 --> 00:21:11.420
you drive them back into
your app to reengage.

00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:13.100
Or if you know
that your users get

00:21:13.100 --> 00:21:15.560
stuck on a particular
level within your game,

00:21:15.560 --> 00:21:18.760
for example, level 10, and they
would go onto Google Search

00:21:18.760 --> 00:21:20.730
to figure out how
to beat level 10,

00:21:20.730 --> 00:21:23.240
you could have an ad that
triggered for the search query,

00:21:23.240 --> 00:21:26.524
"beating Game Of War--
Fire Age, level 10."

00:21:26.524 --> 00:21:28.190
You could direct them
back into your app

00:21:28.190 --> 00:21:30.879
to a page where they could
potentially purchase something

00:21:30.879 --> 00:21:32.420
that would help them
beat that level,

00:21:32.420 --> 00:21:33.961
or take them to a
special level where

00:21:33.961 --> 00:21:36.870
they could progress from there.

00:21:36.870 --> 00:21:39.630
So it's a very, very powerful
way of engaging and tailoring

00:21:39.630 --> 00:21:41.240
your apps to your
specific audience.

00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:45.590
So that's very much
on the Search Network.

00:21:45.590 --> 00:21:47.447
On the display
side of things, we

00:21:47.447 --> 00:21:49.780
fall back on something that's
slightly more traditional.

00:21:49.780 --> 00:21:51.450
And that's remarketing.

00:21:51.450 --> 00:21:55.110
So you can remarket in apps.

00:21:55.110 --> 00:21:56.960
These remarketing
lists are created

00:21:56.960 --> 00:21:58.675
once your app has
been downloaded

00:21:58.675 --> 00:22:01.100
and you add people
to specific lists.

00:22:01.100 --> 00:22:05.200
You can then retarget them while
they're engaging in other apps

00:22:05.200 --> 00:22:07.200
with content that
is relevant to them

00:22:07.200 --> 00:22:08.950
and can help them come
back into your app

00:22:08.950 --> 00:22:11.970
and take a specific action.

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:16.620
I'll give you three examples of
lists that are commonly used.

00:22:16.620 --> 00:22:19.900
So people who didn't use your
app recently-- so your app's

00:22:19.900 --> 00:22:21.130
been downloaded.

00:22:21.130 --> 00:22:22.270
You've taken the effort.

00:22:22.270 --> 00:22:25.000
You pay the money to actually
have your app downloaded.

00:22:25.000 --> 00:22:28.230
But your app hasn't been engaged
with in the past 30 days.

00:22:28.230 --> 00:22:31.160
You could add that cohort of
users to a particular list

00:22:31.160 --> 00:22:33.900
that you could retarget with
messaging that encourages them

00:22:33.900 --> 00:22:36.690
to come back into your app and
either look at a new feature

00:22:36.690 --> 00:22:38.310
or take a particular action.

00:22:38.310 --> 00:22:41.680
But in that way you can
drive that reengagement.

00:22:41.680 --> 00:22:44.011
If people are using a
specific version of your app

00:22:44.011 --> 00:22:46.510
and haven't taken advantage of
some of the cool features you

00:22:46.510 --> 00:22:48.890
might have developed,
you can once again

00:22:48.890 --> 00:22:51.740
tailor a message to
them where you explain

00:22:51.740 --> 00:22:54.770
some of these new features and
what they could potentially

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:59.730
use by going back into
your app and upgrading.

00:22:59.730 --> 00:23:02.380
People who took a specific
action in your app,

00:23:02.380 --> 00:23:04.860
if you know that a
percentage of your app users

00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.510
are the ones that
monetize very well,

00:23:06.510 --> 00:23:08.770
you could add them to
a cohort or a group.

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:11.410
And you could retarget
them with discounts,

00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:13.500
or particular offers,
or new features

00:23:13.500 --> 00:23:15.221
that they could
potentially purchase.

00:23:15.221 --> 00:23:17.220
And in that way you're
really, really increasing

00:23:17.220 --> 00:23:18.696
the lifetime value of that app.

00:23:18.696 --> 00:23:20.070
And that drives
the profitability

00:23:20.070 --> 00:23:21.330
of that app in the long run.

00:23:25.910 --> 00:23:28.580
Now, when you think
of these two combined,

00:23:28.580 --> 00:23:30.680
it becomes very, very powerful.

00:23:30.680 --> 00:23:32.650
So you have the deep
link on one hand,

00:23:32.650 --> 00:23:36.000
and you have the remarketing
and reengagement on the other.

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:38.740
But imagine if you combine
that into one ad format

00:23:38.740 --> 00:23:42.540
where you can tailor and group
people into specific lists.

00:23:42.540 --> 00:23:45.790
You then show them ads that are
very particular to that group,

00:23:45.790 --> 00:23:47.731
and deep link them
back into your app,

00:23:47.731 --> 00:23:49.230
where they can take
actions that are

00:23:49.230 --> 00:23:51.670
very specific to the
particular user group

00:23:51.670 --> 00:23:56.460
that they are and related to
the app where they'll find them.

00:23:56.460 --> 00:23:58.860
It's an incredibly powerful
way of retargeting people

00:23:58.860 --> 00:24:01.790
and increasing that
engagement over time.

00:24:01.790 --> 00:24:03.445
And it's one in
which it's really

00:24:03.445 --> 00:24:05.507
going to drive the lifetime
